      • main

        public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
        The main method for DES+. Reads data from file and then run a simulation based on the input data.
        Parameters:
        args - two arguments, first an integer specifying number of servers in the shop. Second a file containing a sequence of double values, each being the arrival time of a customer (in any order).

      • createScanner

        private static java.util.Optional<java.util.Scanner> createScanner​(java.lang.String[] args)
        Create and return a scanner. If a command line argument is given, treat the argument as a file and open a scanner on the file. Else, create a scanner that reads from standard input.
        Parameters:
        args - The arguments provided for simulation.
        Returns:
        A scanner or null if a filename is provided but the file cannot be open.
